Portugal legendary attacker, Cristiano Ronaldo has stolen the spotlight after it was reported that he wants to leave Manchester United this summer having returned to Old Trafford from Juventus last summer.
However, La Liga Champions, Real Madrid have taken to social media to remember their legend Cristiano Ronaldo, 13 years after he was presented as a Madridista at the Santiago Bernabeu.
Real Madrid posted on Instagram: “#OTD in 2009… We presented @cristiano as a Madridista! Today marks 13 years since the introduction of Cristiano Ronaldo!”
This Instagram post from Real Madrid remembering Cristiano Ronaldo, 13 years after he was presented as a Real Madrid player at the Santiago Bernabeu has attracted reactions from football fans, as some have asked Real Madrid to present him again, while some have called him the greatest player in Real Madrid history.
Here are some screenshots of reactions from football fans:
The Portugal national team captain joined Real Madrid for a world record transfer fee at the time from Manchester United, becoming Real Madrid all-time highest goal scorer and winning numerous award both individually and collectively as a team.



